Defendant David Quince Boyd in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant David Quince Boyd in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.   The Court imposed the following sentence:

The Court imposed 12 months at the House of Correction, with credit for 119 days time served.  Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - No contact with the victim in this case, Tomariel E.;
 - No controlled substances; no alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Restitution set at zero.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit form.
